e \"and\" combiner returns an error, for example: `@media @thinScreen and @shortScreen { .Container { padding: 5px; } }`\n\nYou can copy and paste this more detailed example code into http://less2css.org/ to see the errors on each of the commented out lines.\n\n``` less\n////////////////////////////////////////\n// This portion compiles just fine\n////////////////////////////////////////\n\n@thinScreen: ~\"(max-width: 800px)\";\n@shortScreen: ~\"(max-height: 600px)\"; \n\n/* Match only @thinScreen */\n@media @thinScreen {  .Container { margin-bottom: 80px; } }\n\n/* Match only @shortScreen */\n@media @shortScreen {  .Container { margin-bottom: 20px; } }\n\n/* Match either @thinScreen or @shortScreen */\n@media @thinScreen, @shortScreen { .Container { padding: 20px; } }\n\n// You can combine the Media Query variables within a variable and have it outputted correctly.\n/* Match both @thinScreen AND @shortScreen */\n@tinyScreen: @thinScreen ~\" and \" @shortScreen;\n@media @tinyScreen { .Container { padding: 5px; } }\n\n\n////////////////////////////////////////\n// However, attempting to combine the media queries with \"and\"\n// to match both thin screens and short screens returns an error.\n////////////////////////////////////////\n\n//@media @thinScreen and @shortScreen { .Container { padding: 5px; } }\n//@media @thinScreen ~\"and\" @shortScreen { .Container { padding: 5px; } }\n\n\n//////////////////////////////////////// \n// This issue prevents not just combining media queries, \n// but specifying \"only screen and\" before the variable \n// as well. The following examples all produce errors:\n////////////////////////////////////////\n\n//@media only screen and @thinScreen { }\n//@media ~\"only screen and\" @thinScreen { }\n//@only: ~\"only screen and \";\n//@media @only @thinScreen { };\n\n```\n\nTested in 1.3.3 and 1.4.0 with no luck. Any workarounds other than the combined variable or will this bug just have to be squashed?\n","closed_by":{"login":"lukeapage"